author: thesadefamily
description: Who was drafted by the Yanks?  The game is called over the line. Got to hit the ball on the fly over the line, if it lands over the line and in fair territory without the fielders catching it, it‚Äôs a hit. If it‚Äôs caught or doesn‚Äôt carry the line, it‚Äôs an out. If you hit a foul ball you get one more try. Once you get 2 hits in an inning, every hit after that is a run. A home run is anything past the last fielder wherever they are. Home runs clear the ‚Äúbases‚Äù scoring a run for each plus the batter. You can pitch from wherever you want, and however you want. Most beginners pitch softtoss and swing like baseball. Advanced players have more of a golf/cricket swing to hit the corners. We use an official otl ball made by debeer (or a 16 inch clincher if playing on grass), and wooden softball bats (or metal is playing on grass). The field is 55ft from from the plate, and 55 ft wide. Sidelines extend forever. This year will be the 73nd annual world championship, where hundreds of teams compete over two weekends in July at fiesta island, San Diego. The tournament is two weekends long. It‚Äôs famous for its out of pocket team names and party atmosphere. In this game people swing like golf or cricket because A ground ball is an auto out, pop flies are easy outs. Batting like this allows you to hit low line drives in each corner. All top players hit like this. Most also take a ‚Äúhomerun‚Äù pitch, which they will swing baseball style, if they feel they can hit it past where the last defender is playing (the last defender is the ‚Äúfence‚Äù for a homerun). #baseball #baseballtiktoks #baseballboys #softball #overtheline #otl

description: Welcome to one of the quietest places in the United States ‚Äî the Hoh Rainforest in Olympic National Park.  Tucked away in Washington‚Äôs Olympic Peninsula, this temperate rainforest is not only known for its lush moss-covered trees and misty trails ‚Äî it‚Äôs also renowned for its natural silence. The thick canopy and dense vegetation actually dampen sound, creating a peaceful hush that‚Äôs hard to find anywhere else. This is where you come to hear nothing but nature ‚Äî the soft patter of rain, the rustle of ferns, and maybe the distant call of a bird. It‚Äôs home to the famous ‚ÄúOne Square Inch of Silence‚Äù project, a spot designated to preserve natural quiet. üìçDon't miss the Hall of Mosses Trail for an easy walk through an enchanted green world that feels like stepping into another realm. If you‚Äôre looking for stillness, solitude, and a sensory reset, Hoh Rainforest should be high on your list.
